title: Coffee
description: 20 cm high coffee plant in ceramic pot. This plant prefers place in the shadow and does not need too much water. With the right care you can grow your own coffee. Enjoy!

title: Tea
description: 50 cm high tea plant in ceramic pot. You can prepare your own tea from this plant's leaves. It doesn't need much sunshine, but it's quite thirsty.

title: Pineapple
description: 60 cm high pineapple plant in ceramic pot. Grow your own pineapple! This plant does not need much sunshine, and needs quite little amount of water. After the fruit is ready, the plant dies, but it usually have "baby" plants, so you can have pineapple supply all the time.

title: Banana
description: 20 cm high banana plant in ceramic pot. Grow your own bananas! Banana plant asks for quite a lot of sunshine and quite amount of water, but grows really fast, so you can have your own bananas quickly.

title: Olive
description: 40 cm high olive tree in ceramic pot. With this little tree you can have your own olives. It asks for some sunshine and quite amount of water, but grows really fast.

title: Aloe
description: 60 cm high aloe vera in ceramic pot. This succulent asks for lot of sunshine, but not that much water. It will grow fast. It's gel is used in cosmetics a lot so you can experiment.

title: Chia
description: 60 cm high chia plant, also known as salvia hispanica, in ceramic pot. This plant prefers sunny place and is quite thirsty, but grows really fast and can give you your own chia seeds.

title: Basil
description: 20 cm high basil in ceramic pot. This herb prefers sunny place and is quite thirsty, but grows really fast and can give you your own herb to your meals.

title: Cactus
description: 20 cm high cactus in ceramic pot. Cactus is known for its love of sunny places and does not need much water. It grows pretty fast.

title: Daisy
description: 15 cm high flower in ceramic pot. This nice flower prefers partial shadow and is quite thirsty, but grows pretty fast and makes your room look beautiful. Besides that, you can make tea from its dried flowers.
